# ── Internalconfigf (Vite) only ─────────────────────────────────────────────
# Copy lines you need into .env.local in this folder.

# Vite proxies /api/* to Next (default http://localhost:3000).
# If Next prints another port (e.g. 3001 because 3000 is busy), set:
# VITE_NEXT_ORIGIN=http://localhost:3001
# Then restart dev:all (or restart Vite only).

# Production / preview frontend deployments should call the deployed Next.js app explicitly.
# Example: VITE_API_BASE_URL=https://room-configuration-api.vercel.app
# Leave unset for local same-origin/proxy development.
# VITE_API_BASE_URL=

# Port 3000 already in use (EADDRINUSE on dev:all:3000)?
#   A) Stop the other app on 3000, then: npm run dev:all:3000
#   B) Or: npm run dev:all (auto port) + VITE_NEXT_ORIGIN matching Next’s URL.

# ── Gemini — use repo ROOT .env.local, not this folder ──────────────────────
# IMAGE_GENERATION_API_KEY=your_key_here
# Optional: GEMINI_TEXT_MODEL, GEMINI_IMAGE_MODEL (see ../.env.example)
# Do not use VITE_* for the API key here; /api/generate runs on Next only.

# Edit → Wall/Floor style grid loads mytyles_vitrified_tiles via Next GET /api/mytyles-vitrified-tiles.
# Configure Supabase in the repo root .env.local: NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_URL, NEXT_PUBLIC_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY
# (same keys as the main app). Apply migrations including 008_mytyles_vitrified_tiles*.sql.
